A member, representing AMAC/Bwari Federal Constituency, in the House of Representatives, Hon. Micah Jiba has condoled with the family of a former chairman of Bwari area council, people of his constituency and the All Progressives Congress (APC), on the death of Hon. Isa Dara, in a London hospital after a brief illness. Jiba said he received the news of his death with sadness, adding that Hon. Dara will be greatly missed. “On behalf of the residents of AMAC/Bwari Federal Constituency, we sincerely commiserate with the children, grandchildren and great-grandchildren on demise of their father. He was a leader of inestimable value to FCT. Our constituency and Nigerians will miss him, because of his fatherly role to many people who knew him and the role he played as chairman of Bwari area council, in ensuring the unity of this country.” Jiba, who is also the deputy committee chairman, FCT Area Councils and Auxiliary Matters at the House of Representatives, added that the history of the Bwari area council will forever remember that Dara was a great man and has left an indelible impression and very significant legacy both in the constituency and the minds of his admirers. “We prayed that God will comfort Dara’s family, relatives, friends, associates and admirers, and grant them the fortitude to bear the loss and uncommon vacuum he has left behind. We also pray that God will receive the soul of the late Dara and grant him eternal rest from his long, earthly service to his family, Bwari area council, and the entire FCT,” he stated.